---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="The Orthotic Retail Trap: What Works vs. Gimmicks | Practical Podiatrist">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 text-slate-300 relative z-10">
    <header class="mb-12 border-b border-white/10 pb-8">
      <span class="text-xs font-bold text-accent uppercase tracking-widest block mb-2">Consumer Protection Guide</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white mb-4">Exposing the Orthotic Price Trap</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-400">A 25-year clinical autopsy on multi-thousand-dollar retail gimmicks, cheap pharmacy foam traps, and real arch stabilization.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>In over two decades of active clinical practice, I have witnessed thousands of patients fall victim to high-pressure marketing traps designed to exploit foot pain[cite: 2222, 2223]. You do not need to spend a fortune to get medically sound mechanical relief[cite: 2222].</p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-12">
        <div class="bg-white/[0.02] backdrop-blur-xl border border-red-500/20 p-6 rounded-2xl">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-400 mb-2">⚠️ The Multi-Thousand Dollar Gimmick</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">High-pressure retail outlets (like the Good Feet Store) rely on slick sales pipelines to lock patients into generic plastic insert packages costing thousands[cite: 2222, 2554]. Static footprints onto a pad cannot calculate active joint mechanics[cite: 2224].</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white/[0.02] backdrop-blur-xl border border-yellow-500/20 p-6 rounded-2xl">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-yellow-400 mb-2">☁️ The Pharmacy Soft Foam Trap</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">Drugstore display walls (like standard Dr. Scholl's) trick patients into buying ultra-soft, pillowy gel cushions[cite: 2225]. They feel comfortable for five minutes but compress completely under body weight within days, providing zero structural support[cite: 2225, 2226].</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4 border-l-4 border-teal-400 pl-3">The Store Aisle "Twist Test"</h2>
      <p>Before spending a single dollar on an over-the-counter insert, pick it up and physically attempt to twist it like a wet towel[cite: 2226, 2257]. If the midsection bends easily or folds completely in half like a soft taco, drop it[cite: 2257]. It will collapse completely under your weight[cite: 2257]. Look for a rigid or highly firm polypropylene sub-shell that actively resists twisting forces[cite: 2226, 2257].</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
